# Create Page Guide – Stellar Frontend

Use this guide to create a new page using the existing system. Follow the patterns below.

---

## 1. Project Structure

```
src/
├── pages/              # Page components (one file per page, or folder for complex pages)
│   ├── Accounts.tsx
│   ├── Channels.tsx
│   ├── google/         # Google Ads pages (components/, hooks/, utils/)
│   ├── tiktok/         # TikTok Ads pages (components/tabs/)
│   └── campaigns/      # Campaign detail pages (components/tabs/)
├── services/           # API layer (api.ts base + domain services)
│   ├── googleAdwords/  # Google Ads services (11 files)
│   ├── ai/             # AI assistant services (7 files)
│   └── tiktok/         # TikTok services
├── hooks/              # React Query hooks
│   ├── queries/        # useQuery hooks + queryKeys.ts
│   └── mutations/      # useMutation hooks
├── components/         # Reusable components
│   ├── ui/             # Base UI (Button, Card, Input, Loader, Banner, etc.)
│   ├── layout/         # Sidebar, DashboardHeader, AccountsHeader, Layout, Assistant
│   ├── google/         # Google Ads feature components
│   ├── tiktok/         # TikTok feature components
│   ├── ai/             # AI assistant components
│   ├── filters/        # Filter panel components
│   └── charts/         # Chart/graph components
├── contexts/           # AuthContext, AccountsContext, SidebarContext, DateRangeContext,
│                       # GoogleSyncStatusContext, AssistantContext, GlobalStateContext
├── constants/          # featureFlags.ts, google.ts, googleGeoTargets.ts, etc.
├── types/              # TypeScript type definitions (google/ subdirectory)
├── routes/             # Route definitions (9 files — see §5)
├── utils/              # pageTitle, urlHelpers, formatters, dateHelpers, etc.
└── lib/                # cn.ts (className merger), queryClient.ts
```

---

## 2. Naming Conventions

| Type | Convention | Examples |
|------|-------------|----------|
| **Page file** | PascalCase, descriptive | `Accounts.tsx`, `GoogleCampaigns.tsx` |
| **Page component** | Same as file, exported | `export const Accounts: React.FC = () => {...}` |
| **Service** | camelCase + `Service` or `service` | `accountsService`, `googleAdwordsCampaignsService` |
| **Query hook** | `use` + Entity + Purpose | `useAccountsPaginated`, `useChannels` |
| **Mutation hook** | `use` + Action + Entity | `useCreateAccount`, `useUpdateAccount` |
| **Route path** | kebab-case, nested by domain | `/brands`, `/brands/:accountId/integrations` |

---

## 3. API & Data Fetching

For full API patterns, service modules, React Query hooks, query keys, and mutation patterns, see **`data-layer-guide.mdc`**.

Key points for page development:
- Services live in `src/services/` — import and use with React Query hooks
- Query hooks: `src/hooks/queries/` — wrap service calls in `useQuery`
- Mutation hooks: `src/hooks/mutations/` — wrap create/update/delete in `useMutation`
- Query keys: `src/hooks/queries/queryKeys.ts` — centralized key registry
- Error handling: `err.response?.data?.error ?? err.response?.data?.detail ?? "Request failed"`

